    "description": [
        {
            "text": "The unit $\\textit{Watt Per Square Meter Kelvin }$ ($W m^{-2} K^{-1}$) is a unit in the category of Thermal heat transfer coefficient. \n  It is also known as $\\textit{watt/square meter-kelvin}$. \n  This unit is commonly used in the SI unit system. \n  $\\textit{Watt Per Square Meter Kelvin }$ has a dimension of $MT^{-1}Q^{-1}$ where $M$ is mass, $T$ is time, and $Q$ is temperature. \n  This unit is the standard SI unit in this category.",
            "lang": "en"
        }
